NODE_10_length_81154_cov_798.469911	MetaGeneAnnotator	CDS	16151	17569	.	-	0	ID=MGA_1062;product=MFS transporter;inference=COORDINATES:ab initio prediction:MetaGeneAnnotator,similar to AA sequence:RefSeq:WP_011068650.1;;locus_tag=LOCUS_10550;note=WP_011068650.1 MFS transporter (Bifidobacterium longum) [pid:97.9%25%2C q_cov:100.0%25%2C s_cov:100.0%25%2C Eval:9.1e-263],Domain:cl26210:MFS_2 MFS/sugar transport protein. The Glycoside-Pentoside-Hexuronide (GPH):Cation Symporter Family (TC 2.A.2) GPH:cation symporters catalyze uptake of sugars in symport with a monovalent cation (H+ or Na+). Members of this family includes transporters for melibiose%2C lactose%2C raffinose%2C glucuronides%2C pentosides and isoprimeverose. Mutants of two groups of these symporters (the melibiose permeases of enteric bacteria%2C and the lactose permease of Streptococcus thermophilus) have been isolated in which altered cation specificity is observed or in which sugar transport is uncoupled from cation symport (i.e.%2C uniport is catalyzed). The various members of the family can use Na+%2C H+ or Li%2C Na+ or Li+%2C H+ or Li+%2C or only H+ as the symported cation. All of these proteins possess twelve putative transmembrane a-helical spanners. [Transport and binding proteins%2C Carbohydrates%2C organic alcohols%2C and acids] [Superfamily%2C Aligned:31-460%2C Eval:4.8e-41%2C score:150.1],MGA_1062
